[{"id":"VR619282","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular chamber that contains a block of mass m connected to end of a vertical spring. The other end of the spring is attached to the ceiling of the chamber. The length of the spring is labeled x sub 1. A downward pointing arrow labeled Direction of Velocity is shown to the right of the chamber.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR619282.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> hangs in equilibrium from an ideal spring inside an elevator, as shown. The elevator moves downward at a constant speed and the length of the spring is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. The elevator then gradually slows to a stop with constant acceleration. Which of the following statements correctly describes the length of the spring while the elevator is decelerating?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR619282_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is constant and equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is constant and greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is constant and less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It starts off greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x sub 1\"><math alttext=\"x sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and slowly decreases.</p>"],"answer":1}]